            "value": "A 2022 review across more than thirty studies found that adults who added consistent moderate movement to their week saw average drops in resting systolic blood pressure of about five to eight mmHg over eight to twelve weeks. The biggest gains came from people moving from very little (under three thousand steps a day) to moderate (six to eight thousand a day). Past about nine or ten thousand steps a day, the additional benefit flattened."
